text.tspan: Under-five mortality: IHME vs. UN IGME estimates, 2019
Under-five mortality is the share of newborns who die before reaching the age of five. This compares estimates from
the IHME, Global Burden of Disease study and the UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (IGME).
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019), UN IGME (2023)
